-- Taiwan Stocks: Hon Hai Precision, Motech Industries, Quanta
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-03-30T07:09:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-30/taiwan-stocks-asustek-hon-hai-precision-pegatron-quanta.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index advanced 0.8 percent to 7,933.
The gauge dropped 2.3 percent in March, trimming this quarter’s
gains to 12 percent, the best three-month performance since the
period ended September 2010.  Hon Hai Precision Industry Co. (2317)  (2317 TT), a unit of Foxconn
Technology Group, retreated 1.3 percent to NT$114.50, the most
since March 20. An audit of Foxconn found “serious and
pressing” violations of Chinese  labor laws . Inspectors found at
least 50 breaches of Chinese regulations as well as the code of
conduct Apple signed when it joined the Fair Labor Association
in January after deaths of workers at suppliers, the monitoring
group said today.  Motech Industries Inc. (6244)  (6244 TT), a solar-cell maker,
dropped 3.9 percent to NT$49.20, the lowest close since Dec. 20,
after  Germany ’s parliament approved record cuts for solar- power
incentives, aiming to reduce annual pace of installations by
half.  Quanta Computer Inc. (2382)  (2382 TT) surged 6.9 percent to
NT$77.30, the highest close since April 19, 2002. The world’s
largest laptop maker reported fourth-quarter net income of
NT$6.53 billion ($221 million), higher than the NT$5.52 billion
average of 14 analyst estimates, according to data compiled by
